<paragraph id="007606418FD0FE6048A75088FA95FE3F" blockId="414.[151,1009,1925,1978]" lastBlockId="416.[151,1436,151,824]" lastPageId="416" lastPageNumber="417" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="20D9216F8FD0FE5E48A75088FC54F849" box="[151,1009,1955,1978]" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FD0FE5E48A75088FE40F849" authority="(R. Perkins)" baseAuthorityName="R. Perkins" box="[151,485,1955,1978]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Gonatopus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="414" pageNumber="415" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plebeius">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FD0FE5E48A75088FEC5F84A" box="[151,352,1956,1978]" italics="true" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">Gonatopus plebeius</emphasis>
(R. Perkins)
</taxonomicName>
: 
<treatmentCitation id="816820508FD0FE5E49DF508FFD3AF849" box="[495,671,1955,1977]" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08FD0FE5E49DF508FFD3AF849" author="Olmi" box="[495,671,1955,1977]" firstAuthor="Olmi" page="1647" pageId="414" pageNumber="415" pagination="1 - 1913" refId="ref364993" refString="Olmi, M. (1984) A revision of the Dryinidae (Hymenoptera). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 37, I - XII + 1 - 1913." type="journal article" year="1984">Olmi 1984: 1647</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
; 
<treatmentCitation id="816820508FD0FE5E4A99508FFC54F849" box="[681,1009,1955,1977]" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08FD0FE5E4A99508FFC48F849" author="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" box="[681,1005,1955,1977]" firstAuthor="Guglielmino" page="229" pageId="414" pageNumber="415" pagination="165 - 298" refId="ref360036" refString="Guglielmino, A. &amp; Olmi, M. (1997) A host-parasite catalog of world Dryinidae (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea). Contributions on Entomology, International, 2 (2), 165 - 298." type="journal article" year="1997">Guglielmino &amp; Olmi 1997: 229</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FEEFE6048A757BBFE3FFF40" bold="true" box="[151,410,151,176]" pageId="416" pageNumber="417">Description of female</emphasis>
</treatmentCitation>
</treatmentCitationGroup>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FEEFE604A5957BBFD50FF5F" box="[617,757,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="416" pageNumber="417" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.9">2.9–3.1 mm</quantity>
. Testaceous-reddish, except petiole black, metasoma blackbrown and antennal segments 3–10 brown. Antenna clavate. Head (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FEEFE604BBD5790FBADFF24" box="[909,1032,188,212]" captionStart="PLATE 130" captionStartId="415.[151,233,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[222,1354,207,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-109@415.[202,1385,195,1821]" captionTargetPageId="415" captionText="PLATE 130. A, E. Heads, frontal view. B. Head, dorsal view. C, H. Mesosoma, lateral view. D, F, I. Chelae. G. Mesosoma, dorsal view. A–D. Gonatopus philippinus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. plebeius, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). G–I. G.rufoniger (=G. indianus), holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 1.60 mm for A and B, 0.91 mm for C, 0.19 mm for D, 1.22 mm for E, 0.18 mm for F, 0.61 mm for G and H, 0.25 mm for I." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278832/files/figure.png" pageId="416" pageNumber="417">Plate 130E</figureCitation>
) excavated, shiny, smooth, hairless, unsculptured or weakly granulated; occipital carina absent. Palpal formula 4/2 or 5/2. Pronotum shiny, hairless, unsculptured, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum unsculptured. Metanotum short, about as long as scutellum, not hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum shiny, with anterior surface unsculptured and posterior surface transversely striate. Mesopleuron and metapleuron not transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture obsolete. Segment 1 of protarsus slightly shorter than segment 4 (9:11). Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FEEFE604C835643FA8EFE77" box="[1203,1323,367,391]" captionStart="PLATE 130" captionStartId="415.[151,233,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[222,1354,207,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-109@415.[202,1385,195,1821]" captionTargetPageId="415" captionText="PLATE 130. A, E. Heads, frontal view. B. Head, dorsal view. C, H. Mesosoma, lateral view. D, F, I. Chelae. G. Mesosoma, dorsal view. A–D. Gonatopus philippinus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. plebeius, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). G–I. G.rufoniger (=G. indianus), holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 1.60 mm for A and B, 0.91 mm for C, 0.19 mm for D, 1.22 mm for E, 0.18 mm for F, 0.61 mm for G and H, 0.25 mm for I." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278832/files/figure.png" pageId="416" pageNumber="417">Plate 130F</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and eight–nine peg-like hairs. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FEEFE604C0356B8FB14FE5C" box="[1075,1201,404,428]" captionStart="PLATE 130" captionStartId="415.[151,233,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[222,1354,207,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-109@415.[202,1385,195,1821]" captionTargetPageId="415" captionText="PLATE 130. A, E. Heads, frontal view. B. Head, dorsal view. C, H. Mesosoma, lateral view. D, F, I. Chelae. G. Mesosoma, dorsal view. A–D. Gonatopus philippinus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. plebeius, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). G–I. G.rufoniger (=G. indianus), holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 1.60 mm for A and B, 0.91 mm for C, 0.19 mm for D, 1.22 mm for E, 0.18 mm for F, 0.61 mm for G and H, 0.25 mm for I." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278832/files/figure.png" pageId="416" pageNumber="417">Plate 130F</figureCitation>
) with inner margin proximally serrated, with one row of 13–16 lamellae; distal apex with 10–16 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
